# Investment repo core rules

This repo inherits global Cursor/Codex rules from `~/.cursor/rules/` and `~/.codex/AGENTS.md`. Repo `AGENTS.md` is the local source of truth and must stay in sync with this file.

- Purpose: local read-only Binance technical signal dashboard.
- Never add authenticated exchange access, API keys, real trading execution, order management, withdrawals, or automated exchange trading.
- Local paper-trade tracking is allowed only when it uses live Binance public market prices, not synthetic market data or manual trade uploads.
- Paper trades are spot-style long simulations only. Bearish setups are `risk_off` / `avoid`, never shorts.
- Keep the always-on worker and dashboard sharing SQLite at `data/paper_bot.sqlite`.
- Simulated leverage is research-only and capped at `10x`.
- Keep predictions scenario-based with confidence, confluence, invalidation, and likely zones only.
- Treat Elliott Wave detection as probabilistic.
- Preserve `6h`, `8h`, and `12h` as first-class regime filters.
- Use USDC quote pairs for tracked coins unless the user explicitly requests a different quote asset.
- Keep the key comparison matrix focused on `1h`, `4h`, `12h`, `1d`, and `1w`.
- Keep data access in `src/binance_client.py`, calculations in `src/indicators.py`, signal logic in `src/signals.py`, worker logic in `src/paper_worker.py`, storage in `src/storage.py`, and UI in `app.py`.
- Spot market data should use the configured base URL fallback chain, with `data-api.binance.vision` preferred to avoid regional `451` failures from `api.binance.com`.
- Futures context is optional and must not block the app when `/fapi` endpoints are region-restricted.
- Do not commit unless the user asks.
